On 08-Aug-99 Dan Kegel wrote:
> It appears to be a 100KHz two-wire bus for use wiring up 
> microcontrollers to each other and to peripherals inside
> embedded systems like televisions, etc.
I2C is used for lots of things.  DIMMs, for example, publish their timing
specs over I2C so the memory controller can auto-configure.  It's also used a
lot for things like environment monitoring in enclosures, and LCD displays, etc.
